snippet.title: Hyundai Grand i10 Nios - better than a Swift? | First Drive Review | Autocar India

snippet.title: 2021 MG Astor review – Hello Astor! | First Drive | Autocar India
snippet.description:
The MG Astor is the petrol version of the ZS EV we’re familiar with, and it’s here to rival the Hyundai Creta, Kia Seltos, Volkswagen Taigun, Skoda Kushaq and Nissan Kicks. Nikhil Bhatia experiences all the tech it has to offer and gets a first impression of what the new MG SUV is like to drive. 

MG Astor prices are out! Note, ADAS features available as a paid option on 1.5 CVT Sharp and 1.3 Turbo Sharp variants - 
1.5 MT Style - Rs 9.78 lakh
1.5 MT Super - Rs 11.28 lakh
1.5 MT Smart - Rs 12.98 lakh
1.5 MT Sharp - Rs 13.98 lakh
1.5 CVT Super - Rs 12.68 lakh
1.5 CVT Smart - Rs 14.18 lakh
1.5 CVT Sharp - Rs 14.98 lakh#
1.3 Turbo AT Smart - Rs 15.88 lakh
1.3 Turbo AT Sharp - Rs 16.78 lakh#

#Without ADAS. All prices are ex-showroom, India. 

Cameraperson: Shreyans Chordia
